    "content": "**Geopolitiks Snacks** — April 3, 2026\n\n---\n\n## ✈️ Iran Shot Down a U.S. F-15 and Hit Kuwait's Biggest Refinery (Oil: $109)\n\nDay 35. Iran downed a **U.S. F-15 fighter jet** — one crew member recovered, one still missing and under search-and-rescue. Separately, Iranian drones struck the **Mina Al-Ahmadi refinery in Kuwait** — the country's largest — setting it on fire. Brent crude jumped 7.8% to **$109/barrel**. U.S. gas prices hit **$4.09/gallon nationally**, 37% above pre-war levels.\n\n- A manned F-15 is not a drone. An F-15 going down is a qualitatively different category of escalation from anything in this conflict to date. One aviator is still missing.\n- Kuwait is not party to the US-Iran war. Striking Kuwait's largest refinery is either a deliberate message or a navigational error. Iran says message. Kuwait is considering its options.\n\n*Day 35 of the war that will end \"very shortly\": one missing aviator, $109 oil, Kuwait's refinery on fire. Totally fine.*\n\n**Sources:** [Al Jazeera: Day 35](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/4/3/iran-war-what-is-happening-on-day-35-of-us-israeli-attacks) | [NPR: Iran hits Gulf refineries](https://www.npr.org/2026/04/03/g-s1-116314/iran-hits-gulf-refineries-as-trump-warns-u-s-will-attack-iranian-bridges-power-plants) | [CNN: Iran war live](https://www.cnn.com/2026/04/03/world/live-news/iran-war-us-trump-oil)\n\n---\n\n## 🌉 U.S. Strikes Collapse a Bridge Near Tehran — Then the Pentagon Fires the Army's Top General\n\nU.S. airstrikes destroyed the **B1 bridge between Tehran and Karaj**, killing 8 and injuring 95. The Pasteur Institute — Iran's century-old medical research center — was also hit. Separately, Defense Secretary Hegseth **fired the Army's top general and two senior officers**, mid-war, with no public explanation.\n\n- Striking civilian infrastructure in a capital city — bridge, century-old medical institute — is the kind of escalation that tends to echo in courts and history books long after a conflict ends.\n- Firing your top general during an active military operation is either a sign that things are going very well or very badly. The administration has signaled which framing they prefer.\n\n*Destroying a bridge near Tehran while firing your Army chief. The project plan is proceeding on schedule, apparently.*\n\n**Sources:** [Al Jazeera: Day 35](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/4/3/iran-war-what-is-happening-on-day-35-of-us-israeli-attacks) | [Alma Research: April 3 daily report](https://israel-alma.org/daily-report-the-second-iran-war-april-3-2026-1600/)\n\n---\n\n## 🚢 The UK Is Organizing 40 Countries to Reopen Hormuz (Good Luck With That)\n\nThe UK is coordinating talks with approximately **40 nations** to figure out how to reopen the Strait of Hormuz — through which 20% of global oil and LNG normally flows. Vessel traffic has collapsed from **150/day to 10-20/day** under Iran's effective blockade.\n\n- 40 countries discussing options for a strait controlled by a country currently at war with two of the countries at the table. The menu of options — negotiate, escort, force — all have significant downside scenarios.\n- 10-20 ships per day where 150 used to pass. Maritime insurance for the region is either unavailable or prohibitively priced. The world's energy logistics are running on fumes, more or less literally.\n\n**Sources:** [Al Jazeera liveblog: April 3](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/liveblog/2026/4/3/iran-war-live-trump-warns-assault-on-infrastructure-hasnt-even-started)\n\n---\n\n## 💊 Happy Liberation Day +1: Trump Signs 100% Drug Tariffs (The Previous Ones Were Illegal)\n\nOne year after \"Liberation Day,\" Trump signed **100% tariffs on branded pharmaceutical imports** and overhauled duties on steel, aluminum, and copper — weeks after the Supreme Court declared his previous broad tariffs illegal, triggering a **$166 billion refund process** that everyone agrees is a spectacular mess to unwind.\n\n- The logic: the Supreme Court struck down the last tariffs, so we'll create new ones. The $166B refund is ongoing. The new tariffs haven't been challenged yet. For now.\n- 100% tariffs on branded drug imports: American pharma companies gain a significant moat. American patients gain a bill. Analysts are pricing this in and calling it structural inflation.\n\n*The old tariffs were illegal. The new ones haven't been ruled on yet. Give it a few months.*\n\n**Sources:** [KFGO/AP: Trump drug tariffs](https://kfgo.com/2026/04/02/a-year-after-liberation-day-trump-sets-new-drug-tariffs-adjusts-metals-duties/) | [NPR: tariffs and inflation](https://www.npr.org/2026/04/02/nx-s1-5766424/trump-tariffs-inflation-economy)\n\n---\n\n## 🥚 Zelensky Wants an Easter Ceasefire. Prediction Markets Say 3.5% Odds.\n\nUkraine's President Zelensky proposed an **Easter ceasefire** (April 16). Russia responded by advancing in Donetsk with North Korean troop support. Prediction markets price \"ceasefire by April 30\" at **3.5%**. US-brokered talks have been paused since the Iran war began, and the deal that was 90-95% agreed hasn't moved since.\n\n- 3.5% is roughly the odds markets gave Leicester City to win the Premier League in 2016. One of those bets paid off. Ukraine is watching.\n- Russia deploying North Korean troops in response to a ceasefire proposal is a message. The message is: no.\n\n*\"90% of a peace deal\" and \"0% of an actual ceasefire\" can both be true simultaneously. Welcome to 2026 diplomacy.*\n\n**Sources:** [Russia Matters: war report card April 1](https://www.russiamatters.org/news/russia-ukraine-war-report-card/russia-ukraine-war-report-card-april-1-2026)\n\n---\n\n## 📜 Idaho Signed Four AI Laws. Georgia Adds Three More. The Patchwork Is Growing.\n\nIdaho's governor signed a wave of AI legislation: a **Conversational AI Safety Act**, a synthetic media/voyeurism law, and rules for generative AI in public education. Georgia is wrapping up its legislative session April 6 with three AI bills at the governor's desk — including **SB 444**, which would ban AI-only healthcare insurance decisions.\n\n- Tennessee last week, Idaho this week, Georgia next week. America is building AI regulation state by state, law by law, with no federal framework. Europe has one GDPR. The US is building fifty chatbot safety bills.\n- \"AI systems can't make healthcare insurance decisions alone\" having to be legislated in 2026 is the kind of sentence that deserves a moment of quiet contemplation.\n\n*One GDPR or fifty state chatbot laws. Europe chose one. America is choosing fifty.*\n\n**Sources:** [Transparency Coalition: AI Legislative Update April 3](https://www.transparencycoalition.ai/news/ai-legislative-update-april3-2026)"
